## Interior Point

This ceramic work was inspired by the concept of an interior point in topology.

The piece takes the form of a smooth flying-saucer-like surface without a visible boundary. When learning topology, I often associated interior points with openness and the absence of edges. The small black sphere represents a point that remains entirely surrounded by its neighborhood.

This work is part of a series exploring mathematical concepts through ceramics.
